1. Convert all patient names to uppercase.
ðð®ðžð«ð²: select UPPER(name) from patients

2. Find the length of each staff member's name.
ðð®ðžð«ð²: select staff_name, LEN(staff_name) AS Length from staff

3. Concatenate staff_id and staff_name with a hyphen separator.
ðð®ðžð«ð²: SELECT staff_id, staff_name, CONCAT(staff_id, '-', staff_name) AS staff_identifier
FROM staff;

ðƒðšð¢ð¥ð² ð‚ð¡ðšð¥ð¥ðžð§ð ðž:
Q. Create a patient summary that shows patient_id, full name in uppercase, service in lowercase, age category (if age >= 65 then 'Senior', if age >= 18 then 'Adult', else 'Minor'), and name length. Only show patients whose name length is greater than 10 characters. 

ðð®ðžð«ð²:
SELECT patient_id, UPPER(name) AS full_name_uppercase, LOWER(service) AS service_lowercase, 
 CASE 
 WHEN age >= 65 THEN 'Senior'
 WHEN age >= 18 THEN 'Adult'
 ELSE 'Minor'
 END AS age_category,
 LEN(name) AS name_length
FROM patients
WHERE LEN(name) > 10;
